additionalInfo.description:
Extracts data incrementally from a Salesforce object based on its timestamp and loads it to a dynamically created target.

The Mapping task extracts data from the Salesforce object starting at the last saved timestamp value (ms precision). The last saved timestamp value is stored in in-out parameter, v_max_value.

If you create a relational target, the Mapping task inserts data into the target table the first time it runs. Subsequent runs can load data using update or upsert operations. If you create a flat file target, the Mapping task re-creates the target file each time it runs.
